I don't think relations between LC and Wraith as a whole are bad at all.<br>
<br>
In the past we had run ins, mostly due to Wraith killing a mob LC wanted and LC showing up after we got there and telling us to leave.  Not that Wraith hasn't done that recently to other up and coming guilds.... it's nothing special.  Typical competition between the big uberguild and the up and comer.<br>
<br>
Every time we had a conflict with LC like that, both sides followed up immediatly asking to work it out in the future, get in on rotation or agree not to get in each other's way.<br>
<br>
Wraith has never broken rotation.  Not on ntov, cursed, emp.  <br>
<br>
Individuals in both guilds train.  We don't come to the boards to complain about it much.  <br>
<br>
The hate is about the people that throw stones from glass houses.  We get called zergs, even tho combined with reviv we've never been bigger than LC and rarely much bigger than Vis... We are no more angels than anyone on the server but other folks like to make a huge deal of it here, while we don't.   We take it up with leadership  when we have a problem.<br>
<br>
There is a disctinct difference to me, and to most of my crew... between a guild doing something that conflicts with us, or even doing a blatant jerkoff move.... and hating a guild in perpetuity.  Especially when on the whole we work together and neither side as a whole wants to fight.<br>
<br>
Especially so with individuals... we don't let the bad apples make the reputation for the guild. Generally they don't do more than insult and flame at how cooler they are for joining an established guild than folks like Desi are for leading a crew of folks from Velketor to Vex Thall.<br>
<br>
All the major guilds have members that either bailed from or failed recruiting with one or more of the other guilds.  It's simply not our style to point them out with examples to try to make the other guys look bad.  It's nothing special or unique to any guild.  <br>
<br>
Anyone can pull incidents to make any guild look bad, and every guild will defend what they did as the right thing under the circumstances most of the time.  90% of conflicts are one guild shows up with a small crew, bigger crew shows up to take over,  often the smaller crew has not killed the mob in question before.. often the established power guilds have a rotation claiming that mob that the smaller guild is not a part of.   Most any raiding guild has been on both sides of that conflict and feel totally vicimized or justified on whatever side they fell on at the time.  <br>
<br>
The leadership in both guilds work things out fine, that's all that really matters to me.<br>
<br>
 <p>Gurunt Bangoo &lt;Wraith&gt;<br>
